.TH "bathconvert" 1 "@BATH_DATE@" "BATH @BATH_VERSION@" "BATH Manual"

.SH NAME
bathconvert \- convert profile file to various formats


.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bathconvert
[\fIoptions\fR]
.I hmmfile_out
.I hmmfile_in


.SH DESCRIPTION

.PP
The
.B bathconvert
utility converts an input profile file to different formats.

.PP
By default, the input profile can be in any HMMER/BATH format,
including older ASCII or binary formats. The output is written in
current HMMER3 ASCII format, which is the format used by
.B bathsearch
and other BATH tools.

.PP
.I hmmfile_in
may be '\-' (dash), which means reading this input from stdin rather
than a file.


.SH OPTIONS

.TP
.B \-h
Help; print a brief reminder of command line usage and all available
options.

.TP
.BI \-\-ct " <n>"
Use the alternate genetic code specified by NCBI translation table
number
.IR <n>
when processing the profile. The default is 1 (the standard genetic
code).


.SH SEE ALSO

.BR bathsearch (1),
.BR bathbuild (1),
.BR bathfetch (1),
.BR bathstat (1)

.PP
For complete documentation, see the BATH repository:
https://github.com/TravisWheelerLab/BATH


